                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="15068640" author="garydgregory" created="Tue, 22 Dec 2015 19:51:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you basically saying that &lt;tt&gt;java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantReadWriteLock.ReadLock.lock()&lt;/tt&gt; does not work? That seems hard to believe... what exact version of Java are you using?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15068766" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Tue, 22 Dec 2015 21:36:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The read lock accomplishes nothing. There used to be a write lock as well that was used to allow the manager to be replaced. You removed that method and the write lock in May of 2014. The read lock should have been removed at the same time as it was only there to insure the manager wasn&apos;t changed in the middle of an append.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, there is nothing that makes the manager.write() and manager.flush() act as an atomic operation, so it is possible to have multiple threads calling manager.write() simultaneously, which means more data than was anticipated could be queued for writing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One solution to this would be to introduce a new manager.write method that takes the byte array and a boolean value indicating whether an immediate write is required. Then the locking could be pushed to the appropriate manager if it is required.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15080748" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 4 Jan 2016 06:25:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m working on a patch for this...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15082203" author="garydgregory" created="Tue, 5 Jan 2016 01:47:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed patch. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ralph_goers%40dslextreme.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ralph_goers@dslextreme.com&quot;&gt;ralph_goers@dslextreme.com&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
